    "# <b>boxplot<b>"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "<p style=\"line-height:30px\"><b><font color=\"#999999\" style=\"font-family:Arial; font-size:24px\">fivecentplots.boxplot(df, **kwargs)</font></b><br><b><i>Box plot modeled after the \"Variability Chart\" in JMP which provides convenient, multi-level group labels automatically along the x-axis</i></b><br><br><b>Args:</b><br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>df</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">pandas.DataFrame</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">DataFrame containing data to plot</div></div><br><b>Required Keyword Args:</b><br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>y</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">y-axis column name contining the box plot data</div></div><br><b>Optional Keyword Args:</b><br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><font color=\"#cc00ff\"><i>Basic:</font></i></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>groups</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str | list</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Grouping columns for the box plot. Defaults to None. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Groups>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_on</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle box visibility. Defaults to True. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_divider</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle box divider visibility. Defaults to True. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Dividers>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_divider_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the vertical line between groups. Defaults to #bbbbbb <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#bbbbbb;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_divider_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box divider lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to -. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_divider_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the divider lines in pixels. Defaults to 1 </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_edge_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the edge of the box. Defaults to #aaaaaa <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#aaaaaa;display:inline-block\"></span>. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/styles.html#Boxplot-example>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_edge_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the edge of the boxes in pixels. Defaults to 0.5 </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_fill_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string of the bar fill . Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/styles.html#Boxplot-example>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_median_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string of the median line inside each box. Defaults to #ff7f0e <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ff7f0e;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_range_lines</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle the horizontal lines showing the min/max of the data range. Defaults to True. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Range-lines>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_range_lines_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the box range lines. Defaults to #cccccc <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_range_lines_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box range lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to --. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_range_lines_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the range lines in pixels. Defaults to 1 </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_whisker</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle range lines that extend from the box Q1/Q3 edges to the data min/max. Defaults to True. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Whiskers>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_whisker_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the box whisker lines. Defaults to #cccccc <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_whisker_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box whisker lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to -. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_whisker_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the whisker lines in pixels. Defaults to 0.5 </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Set the fractional width of the boxes between 0-1. Defaults to 0.5 [if violin on, 0.15]. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>notch</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Use a notched-style box instead of a rectangular box. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Notch>See example</a> </div><br><font color=\"#cc00ff\"><i>Grouping text:</font></i> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_fill_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for group label fill between 0-1. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_fill_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the group label background color. Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_edge_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for group label line edge between 0-1. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_edge_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the edge of the line around the group labels in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_edge_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the group label rectangle edge. Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_font</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font name for box group label. Defaults to Sans-serif </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_font_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for group label font. Defaults to #000000 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#000000;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_font_size</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font size for group label text in pixels. Defaults to 14. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_font_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font style for the group label text {\"normal\", \"italic\", \"oblique\"}. Defaults to \"normal’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_label_font_weight</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font weight for the group label text {\"light\", \"normal\", \"medium\", \"semibold\", \"bold\", \"heavy\", \"black\"}. Defaults to \"normal’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_fill_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for group title fill between 0-1. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_fill_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the group title background color. Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_edge_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for group title line edge between 0-1. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_edge_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the edge of the line around the group titles in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_edge_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the group title rectangle edge. Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_font</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font name for box group title. Defaults to Sans-serif </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_font_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for group title font. Defaults to #000000 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#000000;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_font_size</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font size for group title text in pixels. Defaults to 14. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_font_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font style for the group title text {\"normal\", \"italic\", \"oblique\"}. Defaults to \"normal’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_title_font_weight</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Font weight for the group title text {\"light\", \"normal\", \"medium\", \"semibold\", \"bold\", \"heavy\", \"black\"}. Defaults to \"normal’. </div><br><font color=\"#cc00ff\"><i>Stat Lines:</font></i> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_mean</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of a line showing the mean of all data on the plot. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Grand-Mean/Median>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_mean_color | grand_mean_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the grand mean line. Defaults to #555555 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#555555;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_mean_style | grand_mean_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box grand mean lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to \"-’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_mean_width | grand_mean_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the grand mean line in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_median</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of a line showing the median of all data on the plot. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Grand-Mean/Median>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_median_color | grand_median_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the grand median line. Defaults to #0000ff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#0000ff;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_median_style | grand_median_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box grand median lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to \"-’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_grand_median_width | grand_median_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the grand median line in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_mean</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of a line showing the mean of each data group on the plot. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Group-Means>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_mean_color | group_mean_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the group mean line. Defaults to #555555 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#555555;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_mean_style | group_mean_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the box group mean lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to \"-’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_group_mean_width | group_mean_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the group mean line in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_stat_line</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Set the statistic for the connecting line {‘mean’, ‘median’, ‘std’, ‘qXX’ [qunatile where XX is a number between 0-100]}. Defaults to mean. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Stat-line>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_stat_line_on</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of the stat line between boxes. Defaults to True. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_stat_line_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the stat line. Defaults to #666666 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#666666;display:inline-block\"></span> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_stat_line_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the stat line in pixels. Defaults to 1. </div><br><font color=\"#cc00ff\"><i>Diamonds:</font></i> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds | mean_diamonds</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of a diamond overlay on the box showing the group mean and a confidence interval. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Mean-Diamonds>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_alpha | mean_diamonds_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for the diamonds between 0-1. Defaults to 1. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_edge_color | mean_diamonds_edge_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the edges of the diamond. Defaults to #FF0000 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#FF0000;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_edge_style | mean_diamonds_edge_style</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Line style for the diamonds lines {‘-’, ‘--’, ‘-.’, ‘:’}. Defaults to \"-’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_edge_width | mean_diamonds_edge_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Width of the diamond lines in pixels. Defaults to 0.7. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_fill_color | mean_diamonds_fill_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the fill of the diamond. Defaults to None. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_mean_diamonds_width | mean_diamonds_width</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Set the fractional width of the diamonds between 0-1. Defaults to 0.8. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>conf_coeff</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Confidence interval from 0 to 1. Defaults to 0.95. </div><br><font color=\"#cc00ff\"><i>Violins:</font></i> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>box_violin | violin</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of violin plot showing the distribution of box plot data. Defaults to False. <br><a href=https://endangeredoxen.github.io/fivecentplots/0.5.0/boxplot.html#Violins>See example</a> </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_box_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the fill of an optional box overlay on the violin. Defaults to #555555 <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#555555;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_box_on</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of a box over the violin plot. Defaults to True. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_edge_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the edge of the violins. Defaults to #aaaaaa <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#aaaaaa;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_fill_alpha</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">float</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Transparency value for the violin plots between 0-1. Defaults to 0.5. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_fill_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the fill of the violins. Defaults to fcp.DEFAULT_COLORS <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#4b72b0;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#c34e52;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#54a767;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#8172b1;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#64b4cc;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ccb973;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#fa8d62;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#8d9fca;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#a6d753;display:inline-block\"></span><span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#fed82f;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_markers</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">bool</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Toggle visibility of data point markers on the violin plots. Defaults to False. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_median_color</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Hex color string for the median point in each violin. Defaults to #ffffff <span id=\"rectangle\" style=\"height: 12px; width: 12px; background-color:#ffffff;; border: 1px solid #cccccc;display:inline-block\"></span>. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_median_marker</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">str</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Marker type for the median point in each violin. Defaults to \"o’. </div></div><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\"><b>violin_median_size</b> (<i><font color=\"#0c9c6e\">int</font></i>):<br><div style=\"padding-left: 30px\">Size of the median point marker in each violin. Defaults to 2.</div></div></p>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "## Groups"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "One of the most powerful features of JMP is its variability chart, which partitions data into separate boxplots based on one or more grouping criteria.  <b><i><font color=\"#4d5a91\">fivecentplots </font></i></b> achieves this characteristic via the keyword `groups`.  The value of this keyword is one or more column names from the `DataFrame` that differentiate the `y` values being plotted."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Single group"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Using our fake dataset, we first plot our data grouped by a single column named \"Batch\".  Because our dataset has 3 unique values in the \"Batch\" column, we get three boxplots, each with a descriptive label."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([101, 106, 103])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df.Batch.unique()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 529.5x447.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups='Batch')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Multiple groups"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can dive deeper into the dataset by specifying a list of column names for `groups`.  In this example we use columns \"Batch\" and \"Sample\" for which there are 7 unique groups.  Notice that the order of the values passed to `groups` determines the grouping hierarchy, with the first grouping column values on the bottom of the plot.\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"admonition note\">\n",
    "<p class=\"admonition-title\"></p>\n",
    "<p>Note that for purposes of the boxplot API, the values in the white rectangles under the plotting area are styled via keywords prefixed with `box_group_label`, while the column name strings are styled via keywords prefixed with `box_group_title`.</p>\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Box elements"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Several descriptive elements are available within the boxplot to better visualize the dataset.  These features are illustrated below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Dividers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "By default, when multiple `groups` are specified gray divider lines are drawn between the bottom-level groups.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "These divider lines can be disabled or styled using the appropriate keywords.\n",
    "\n",
    "Disabled:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_divider=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Styled:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], \n",
    "            box_divider_color='#d42269', box_divider_width=10, box_divider_style='--')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Whiskers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The \"whiskers\" on a boxplot span from Q1 to the minimum value on the lower end and Q3 to the maximum on the upper end, excluding outliers.  Outliers are defined as any points that are below (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) on the lower end and above Q3 to (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR) on the upper end.  In the example below, notice that the first and second boxes each have an outlier point outside of the blue whisker lines.  Whisker lines can be styled using the keywords prefixed by `box_whisker`.  Note the horizontal \"cap\" at the end of the whisker lines shares the same style as the whiskers themselves. Default behavior is a solid gray line 0.5 pixel in width.\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"admonition note\">\n",
    "<p class=\"admonition-title\"></p>\n",
    "<p>The dashed lines that span to the outlier points are controlled by `box_range_lines` described in the next section.</p>\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df=df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'],\n",
    "            box_whisker_color='#0000FF', box_whisker_width=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Whiskers can be disabled (be careful with the lack of plurality in the prefix!) but beware that if the range lines are still enabled you will see similar lines and horizontal caps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_whisker=False, box_range_lines=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Range lines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Outlier points by definition fall outside of the box whiskers, but with range lines we can span the entire range of the data (from absolute minimum to absolute maximum).  This is particularly useful to indicate when there are outlier data points that fall outside of the limits of the visible y-axis.  These range lines are enabled by default but can be disabled or styled through keywords with the prefix `box_range_lines`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Default behavior is a dashed gray line 0.5 pixel in width:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_whisker=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If we disable range lines and leave whiskers enabled we get this:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_range_lines=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Styled:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

    "            box_range_lines_color='#d42269', box_range_lines_width=10, box_range_lines_style='-.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Markers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Comment on box_ prefix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Jitter"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To improve visibility of the actual data points in the boxplots, <b><i><font color=\"#4d5a91\">fivecentplots </font></i></b> automatically jitters the data points (i.e., adds some random noise along the x-axis).  This can be disabled using the keyword `jitter`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], jitter=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## More grouping"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Legend"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Boxplots also support legending for another level of data visualization:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 612.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], legend='Region')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note:  if there are a lot of legend items, the position of the legend will be automatically adjusted to avoid rendering over the box group titles."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 560.5x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df['Row'] = [int(f) for f in df.index / 4]\n",
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], legend='Row')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Column plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "boxplots can also be broken into subplots based on \"row\" and/or \"col\" values or \"wrap\" keywords.  In each case, a column name in the `DataFrame` is supplied as the keyword value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 774.375x409 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], col='Region', ax_size=[300, 300])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Row plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 444.375x738.209 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], row='Region', ax_size=[300, 300])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Wrap plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 744.375x944.044 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Sample', 'Region'], wrap='Batch', ax_size=[300, 300])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Alternatively, we can wrap multiple `y` column values and create a unique subplot for each column:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 812.375x462.061 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Make a new y column\n",
    "df['Value*2'] = 2*df['Value']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot\n",
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y=['Value', 'Value*2'], groups=['Batch', 'Sample', 'Region'], wrap='y', \n",
    "            ax_size=[300, 300])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Or if we disable y-axis range sharing:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 812.375x462.061 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y=['Value', 'Value*2'], groups=['Batch', 'Sample', 'Region'], wrap='y', \n",
    "            ax_size=[300, 300], share_y=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Stats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Grand Mean/Median"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The \"grand mean\" or \"grand median\" is the mean/median value for the entire data set in a given plot window.  By default, the \"grand mean\" line is a dashed gray line and the \"grand median\" is a dashed blue line.  Individual line color, styles, and widths can be controlled via the typically-named keywords prefixed by `box_grand_mean` or `box_grand_median`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], grand_mean=True, grand_median=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " Both long form and short form keywords are available: i.e., `box_grand_mean_ATTRIBUTE` or `grand_mean_ATTRIBUTE`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], grand_mean=True, \n",
    "            grand_mean_style=':', grand_mean_color='#FF0000', box_grand_mean_width=0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Group Means"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Group means that correspond to the first level of grouping (i.e., same as the vertical divider lines).  By default, the mean values are depicted with horizontal dashed magenta lines.  Style are controlled by ``box_group_means_ATTRIBUTE`` or ``group_means_ATTRIBUTE``."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], group_means=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Mean Diamonds"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The ``box_mean_diamonds`` or ``mean_diamonds`` keyword allows you to overlay a diamond on the box which shows vertically the span of the data for a given confidence interval (default = 95%) and a horizontal line for the mean value of each group.  Using default parameters the diamonds are green (like the program that inspired them :) )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], mean_diamonds=True, conf_coeff=0.95)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Stat line"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In addition to displaying boxes with a median line and interquartile ranges, a connecting line can be drawn between boxes at some statistical value.  By default, the line connects the mean value of the distribution for each box, but other `DataFrame` stat values can be selected.  The stat line accepts the typical styling keywords of any line object with the prefix `box_stat_line` (i.e., `box_stat_line_color` or `box_stat_line_width`)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_stat_line='mean')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Median"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_stat_line='median')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "#### Quantile"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To define a quantile, use the convention \"q{number between 0-100}\":"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], box_stat_line='q95')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Violins"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also plot distributions with violin plots that show kernal density estimates of the data.  By default, these violin plots also contain a small boxes with whiskers to indicate Q1, Q3, 1.5 * IQR, and the median of the distribution (the white point).  Discrete data points are disabled by default but can be turned on with the keyword `violin_markers=True` (default box style shamelessly appropriated from `seaborn`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], violin=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can change the style of the violin density profiles <i>and</i> the associated boxplot using keywords starting with `violin`. Note that the standard box styling attributes are ignored when adding the violin plot.  The reason for this is to make it possilbe to maintain different default settings for regular box plots and violin plots in the same theme file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], violin=True, \n",
    "            violin_fill_color='#eaef1a', violin_fill_alpha=1, violin_edge_color='#555555', violin_edge_width=2,\n",
    "            violin_box_color='#ffffff', violin_whisker_color='#ff0000', \n",
    "            violin_median_marker='+', violin_median_color='#00ffff', violin_median_size=10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also disable the box overlay on the violin plot as follows:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 544.375x469.455 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fcp.boxplot(df, y='Value', groups=['Batch', 'Sample'], violin=True, violin_box_on=False, violin_markers=True, jitter=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
